title: Microsoft Windows: Update
agents: windows
catalog: os/misc
license: GPLv2
distribution: Christopher Pommer
description:
 This check monitors the pending Windows Updates from a Windows host.

 The service is in state {OK} if there are no pending updates.
 You can configure threshold levels for pending updates and you can define
 update name patterns to be ignored.

 You have to deploy the agent script {ms_win_update.ps1} to the host.

discovery:
 A service named {Windows update} is created for the pending Windows updates
 on each host on which you have deployed the agent script.